{
  "stem": "18470.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then eventually they were removed and went to Theresienstadt and Auschwitz, and other concentration camps subsequently.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the systematic policy of deprivation of income, harassment, physical punishment through beating, all kinds of illegal and horrible ways to deal with people, were visited upon the Jewish community, which had lived for hundreds of years in this town, and was visited upon them by their neighbors, some neighbors.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Other neighbors, I know when I went back, we heard stories of people who risked their reputation or lives for bringing food to their Jewish neighbors.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In one instance, a hole was battered through the basement walls.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And neighbors brought food that were-- was delivered to this Judenhaus, so they didn't starve completely.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "On the other hand, they couldn't give them too much food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because then it would become obvious that food was being made available to them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then there was, of course, women were not permitted to keep any jewelry, except their wedding rings.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I remember my-- my mother giving up all of her gold jewelry, my grandmother's jewelry, my aunt's, the silverware, and it was put into a pillow case, which I dragged down to the district office of the police station.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And for which they, in their fastidious way, gave me a receipt, which of course was totally worthless.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They had no intention of ever returning any of this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But the receipt, they said, was very important.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "You might need it one day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You needed it to get out of the country.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "If you did get a visa to a foreign country, and you got an exit visa from Germany, then you had to show that you had complied with the law by having surrendered all your worldly goods.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
